<h3 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ff0000;">COFFEE WITH COUNCIL</span></h3>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong><span style="color: #000000;">It was great to see so many residents at last night's Coffee with Council meeting. Thank you for coming out and we hope that you found the meeting as valuable as we did.</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong><span style="color: #000000;">We are striving to be available and transparent to you as much as possible as we value your input, creativity and suggestions. </span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong><span style="color: #000000;">Additionally, we will be meeting again August 18, stay tuned for location.</span></strong></span><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong><span style="color: #000000;"><br /></span></strong></span></p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ff0000;">2016 SPRING ROAD RESTRICTIONS WITHIN THE TOWN OF SAINTE-ANNE</span></h3>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Please be aware the annual spring road restrictions will be applied to all streets within the boundaries of the Town of Sainte-Anne. Exempt from these Town restrictions are Centrale Ave. and TraverseRoad, as they will be restricted as requied by Manitoba Highways&nbsp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Spring road restriction is 65% of normal load axle units.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Town of Sainte-Anne spring road restriction is in effect <strong>March 14 at 6:00 am</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong>Provincial road restrictions is in effect <strong>March 11 at 6:00 am</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong>To view more details please visit this web site <a href="http://www.gov.mb.ca/mit/srr/">http://www.gov.mb.ca/mit/srr/</a></p>
<h3>TEXT - EMAIL UPDATES</h3>
<p>Are you interested in getting quick easy text or emails to keep you updated on activities, events, important information and dates from the Town of Ste. Anne, follow these easy instructions to sign up for these important updates.</p>
<p>To receive a message via text: &nbsp;text @town-ville to 204 800-5926 you will be asked to enter your name (of your choice) its that easy!! (you can opt-out at anytime by replying, 'unsubscribe @town-ville')</p>
<p>To receive a message via email, send an emai to town-ville@mail.remind.com &nbsp;To unsubscribe, reply with 'unsubscribe' in the subject line.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 12px; text-align: left;">Welcome to the Town of Ste. Anne's new website, where you will find useful information pertaining to our town. We hope you find what you are looking for, and any feedback is appreciated! Please </span><a style="text-align: left;" href="../page.php?id=12">contact us</a><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 12px; text-align: left;"> with any questions or requests that you may have.</span></p>
